This paper is about a consensus protocol for wide-area network (WAN) deployments, which involves distributed systems and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the partitioning of object-space and the use of quorums, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of phase-1 and phase-2 of Paxos, which are related to operating systems, suggesting that cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possible category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AWS regions, which is related to network infrastructure, suggesting that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance evaluation of the protocol, which is related to systems and control, suggesting that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category.
